de.awi.floenavigation.aismessages

Class AIVDM

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.awi.floenavigation.aismessages.AIVDM

  • public class AIVDM
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is called from AISDecodingService to segregate the ASCII packet on the basis of comma. The payload is segregated from the entire packet sequence and used for further processing.

      • channelCode

        private char channelCode
        Stores the radio channel code. AIS uses the high side of the duplex from two VHF radio channels: AIS Channel A is 161.975Mhz (87B); AIS Channel B is 162.025Mhz (88B).

      • strbuildtodec

        static <T> java.lang.Object strbuildtodec(int begin,
                                          int end,
                                          int len,
                                          java.lang.StringBuilder binLocal,
                                          java.lang.Class<?> type)
        Generic function implemented to process the payload Receives the binary data and splits according to the begin and the end index and converts to a decimal value which represents a valid data for the various fields of the AIS payload
        Type Parameters:
        T - Generic data type (template concept of java)
        Parameters:
        begin - index of the beginning of a member of the AIS payload
        end - index of the end of a member of the AIS payload
        len - represents the length of the member
        binLocal - Binary equivalent of the payload
        type - Datatype value used to truncate the data field as per the datatype value expected from the calling function
        Returns:
        returns the decimal equivalent
